
[1]apportion

   APPO'RTION, v.t. [L. ad and portio, portion. See Portion and Part.]

   To divide and assign in just proportion; to distribute among two or
   more, a just part or share to each; as, to apportion undivided rights;
   to apportion time among various employments.
